Subject: Re: [T2] How not to sell a VW van-a sour experience

> They claimed to have to gotten power of attorney from the grandfather "in Florida" to retitle the van in one of their names- I don't think it can be done that fast- don't you need a lawyer at both ends?

The DMV in most states and Florida for certain have a simple form for
power of attorney for title.  All it needs is a notarized signature
from the title holder.

Mind you, that would still require and overnight shipment of the
document at bare minimum... But it's not hard.
